Wikidata is a free, collaborative, multilingual secondary knowledge base that collects structured data—items identified by Q‑numbers, each with labels, descriptions, aliases, and statements composed of P‑numbered properties and values—to support Wikipedia, other Wikimedia projects, and any external applications.  Items are centrally stored in the Wikidata repository, linked to each other, to external identifiers, and to corresponding pages on client wikis via sitelinks, allowing the same data to be displayed in any language and kept up‑to‑date across all projects.  Users and bots can create, edit, and query this data through built‑in tools (e.g., the Query Service), APIs, or Lua interfaces, making the information readily reusable worldwide.
